    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>SONY TO INCREASE CHIP OUTPUT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Stephanie Strom</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Strom, Stephanie</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Sony Corp will spend 125 billion yen, or $1.15 billion, to increase production of chips for its new PlayStation 2 video game console (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Sony said it would spend 125 billion yen, or $1.15 billion, to increase production of the chips that are the heart and soul of its new PlayStation 2 video game console. The company plans to more than double its production of the eight-inch silicon wafers by next June, in an effort to ensure that it does not run into shortages like those that bedeviled its competitors, Nintendo and Sega. Sony said it wanted to increase production of PlayStation 2 to 1.4 million units a month, compared with its current monthly output of 500,000 units.</p>
        <p>Stephanie Strom</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Sony said it would spend 125 billion yen, or $1.15 billion, to increase production of the chips that are the heart and soul of its new PlayStation 2 video game console. The company plans to more than double its production of the eight-inch silicon wafers by next June, in an effort to ensure that it does not run into shortages like those that bedeviled its competitors, Nintendo and Sega. Sony said it wanted to increase production of PlayStation 2 to 1.4 million units a month, compared with its current monthly output of 500,000 units.</p>
        <p>Stephanie Strom</p>
